    "body": "Even though the following code compiles with `--cfg=miri` enabled, and `miri.rs` is choosen on x64, which is great\n\n```rust\n#[cfg_attr(miri, path = \"miri.rs\")]\n#[cfg_attr(target_arch = \"x86_64\", path = \"x64.rs\")]\nmod m;\n```\n\nIt'd not be forward compatible:\n\n```rust\ncfg-miri $ RUSTFLAGS=--cfg=miri cargo r\n   Compiling cfg-miri v0.1.0 (/home/gh-zjp-CN/tmp/cfg-miri)\nwarning: unused attribute\n --> src/main.rs:6:36\n  |\n6 | #[cfg_attr(target_arch = \"x86_64\", path = \"x64.rs\")]\n  |                                    ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ help: remove this attribute\n  |\nnote: attribute also specified here\n --> src/main.rs:5:18\n  |\n5 | #[cfg_attr(miri, path = \"miri.rs\")]\n  |                  ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n  = warning: this was previously accepted by the compiler but is being phased out; it will become a hard error in a future release!\n  = note: `#[warn(unused_attributes)]` (part of `#[warn(unused)]`) on by default\n```\n\nSo each current cfg_attr must exclude miri explicitly.\n\n```diff\n#[cfg_attr(miri, path = \"miri.rs\")]\n-#[cfg_attr(target_arch = \"x86_64\", path = \"x64.rs\")]\n+#[cfg_attr(all(target_arch = \"x86_64\", not(miri)), path = \"x64.rs\")]\nmod m;\n```",
